Ing '''Van''' ([[Turkish language|Turkish]]: ''Van'', {{lang-ota|وان}}, {{lang-hy|Վան}} ''Van'',<ref>[http://slovari.yandex.ru/dict/geography/article/geo/geo1/geo-0832.htm?text=%D0%B2%D0%B0%D0%BD%20%D1%82%D1%83%D1%80%D1%86%D0%B8%D1%8F Slovar sovremennikh geographicheskikh nazvaniy (in Russian)] / Ed. by acad. V.M. Kotliakov, [[Yekaterinburg]], U-Faktoria, 2006</ref> {{lang-ku|Wan}}) metung yang lakanbalen king mawli-aslagang (southeastern) [[Turkey]] ampong buntukbalen ning lalawigan ning [[Van Province|Van]], nung nu deng lahing [[Kurdish]] ing mayorya <ref>State-Tribe Relations: Kurdish Tribalism in the 16th-and 17th-Century Ottoman Empire, H Ozoglu - British Journal of Middle Eastern Studies, 1996 - JSTOR</ref>, at atyu king aslagang pangpang (eastern shore) ning [[Lake Van]]. Ing opisyal a populasyun ning lakanbalen anyang 2010 367,419,<ref>[http://report.tuik.gov.tr/reports/rwservlet?adnksdb2=&report=idari_yapi_09sonrasi.RDF&p_il1=65&p_yil=2009&p_dil=1&desformat=html&ENVID=nufus2000db2Env]</ref> oneng mas matas la reng dakal a tantya, alimbawa ing metung anyang 1996, a 500,000<ref>David McDowall, "Modern History of the Kurds," I.B. Tauris, 1996, pg 440</ref>, ampo ing sasabyan ning sadyang Mayor a Burhan Yengun a sínabi kanung miras yang 600,000.<ref>TESEV. "An Assessment of the Van Action Plan for the Internally Displaced" Accessed at http://www.tesev.org.tr/UD_OBJS/PDF/DEMP/TESEV_VanActionPlanReport.pdf.</ref>

